  "narrative_arc": "Wealthy, beautiful, bereaved woman who decides to sleep for a year using a cocktail of prescription drugs. Moshfegh documents the pharmacy of privilege — a compliant psychiatrist, unlimited prescriptions, a rent-free apartment. Her dome is filled with resources and empty of meaning.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "This is a wealthy dome — Layer 3 (Fiscal) is maximized, Layer 5 (Housing) is secure, but Layers 10-12 are in crisis. Her dome proves that filling lower layers doesn't guarantee flourishing. The COSM score for a rich, devastated person reveals the system's blind spots.",
